    At{Lasham Pumping Station,}        
 water is pumped through{bore holes}   
 in the ground,which is then pumped    
 up two hundred and forty feet.        
    All the water pumped is tap water. 
    The station can pump{sixty         
{thousand}gallons an hour.That is{     
{twenty two}litres a second.           
    Then the water is pumped to{       
{Crondall,Ewshott,}the back of{        
{Farnborough,Bentworth,Medstead}and    
{Elisfield.                            
{   Lasham}means{"Pond on the Hill".
